review_blob: Sweet aroma, very low hop aroma. Nice straw yellow color, white head, dissipated quickly. Funky taste, almost condensation like tasting, possible sanitation and cleaning problem. Thought it may have been a different hop variety, but not, possible musty grain? Off flavors though. Nice and light on the palate, crisp finish with a grainy malty flavor through the nose. I love the Helles style, and this was not as enjoyable as I was expecting.

Aroma swells of grapefruit, slight wet fur aroma reminds me of fido in the rain, but may be the glass. Appearance a nice golden color. Tastes fruity and floral citrus on the buds and carbonation cleanses the palate. Overall beautiful beer, though definitely not the Brown Shugga substitute I was expecting.
Beautiful tobacco aromatic coming off this beer. Would almost say its equivalent to a christmas strong Scottish ale, but without the smokiness.
